          From his position,
          the captain of the HMS Sasquatch finds the signal flare to be at a bearing of N<m>75^{\circ}</m>W. If the SS Bigfoot is 5 miles from the HMS Sasquatch and the bearing from the SS Bigfoot to the HMS Sasquatch is N<m>50^{\circ}</m>E, find the distances from the flare to each vessel,
          rounded to the nearest tenth of a mile.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          The SS Bigfoot is about 4.1 miles from the flare.
          The HMS Sasquatch is about 2.9 miles from the flare.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
